<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>rest room <i>(UK)</i> • rest room <i>(U.S.)</i></xh5><p> <i>rest room (UK)—</i>a room in a public building set aside for staff to take their breaks in: The suite consisted of the operating room, the anesthetic room, the scrub-up room and the doctors’ <u>rest room</u>.</p><p><i>rest room (U.S.)—</i>a room in a public place, containing a toilet: I told them about my difficulty locating the <u>restroom</u> in the restaurant. They said, “You can’t say restroom or bathroom in Europe.”</p> </entry>
